headline: Smurfit Westrock (NYSE:SW) Valuation Check After Recent Pullback And Perceived 21.5% Undervaluation
summary: Why Smurfit Westrock Is On Investors’ Radar Today Smurfit Westrock (SW) has attracted fresh attention after recent trading, with the share price closing at $41.63 and short term returns showing mixed moves over the past week and month. For context, the packaging group reports annual revenue of about $31.1b and net income of $748.0m, which gives investors a sense of its current scale and earnings base in the paper based packaging sector.
